---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ProjectHero from "../components/ProjectHero.astro";
---

<Layout
	title="Adrenaline"
	description="Adrenaline is a lightweight Minecraft modpack that heavily improves FPS and logic performance through various optimization mods."
	style="adrenaline"
>
	<ProjectHero
		logo="/branding/adrenaline/text-logo.svg"
		alt="Adrenaline"
		logoHeight="h-24"
		background="/branding/adrenaline/background.svg"
		mainLinks={[
			{
				href: "/adrenaline/installation",
				icon: "lucide:download",
				label: "Install",
			},
			{
				href: "/adrenaline/installation",
				icon: "lucide:book",
				label: "Wiki",
			},
			{
				href: "https://github.com/skywardmc/adrenaline/issues",
				icon: "lucide:circle-dot",
				label: "Issues",
			},
		]}
		socialLinks={[
			{
				href: "https://modrinth.com/project/adrenaline",
				icon: "simple-icons:modrinth",
				label: "Modrinth",
			},
			{
				href: "https://github.com/skywardmc/adrenaline",
				icon: "simple-icons:github",
				label: "GitHub",
			},
		]}
	>
		A lightweight, open-source performance modpack for Minecraft
	</ProjectHero>

	<section class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-full">
		<p>
			Adrenaline is a lightweight, open-source modpack that significantly
			improves Minecraft render and logic performance through various different
			mods and configurations. You can install it on either your client or
			server - installation instructions are below.
		</p>
		<p>
			The aim of this project is to make the game run as well as possible while
			being stable enough for production use. It's default installation is very
			minimal for flexibility, so you may want to install some of your own mods
			afterwards, such as Mod Menu or Sodium Extra.
		</p>
		<p>
			Here is the <a href="/adrenaline/performance-features">list of mods</a> used
			to improve performance. Some mods are only installed depending on the environment
			you install it in, such as a server or client. Benchmarks are not provided as
			it can significantly differ depending on device, so I'd suggest you try it out
			yourself.
		</p>
		<p>
			For more information, read through Adrenaline's <a
				href="https://modrinth.com/project/Adrenaline">Modrinth</a
			> page.
		</p>
		<h2>Installation</h2>
		<p>
			If you want to install Adrenaline, see the <a
				href="/adrenaline/installation">Adrenaline/Installation</a
			> page.
		</p>
	</section>
</Layout>
